Hamstrung from the start by the refusal of the United States, Russia and China to join, the court has since faced criticism for having mainly taken on cases from poorer African nations. The court has permitted Chief Prosecutor Fatou Bensouda to investigate atrocities allegedly committed by Israeli soldiers. Ongwen, who surrendered in 2015, is the first LRA commander to be put on trial and convicted by the ICC. Nyali MP Mohamed Ali's action resulted in a debate about safety as political temperatures rise ahead of the 2022 poll. President Kenyatta says one cannot "insult people" while also taking credit for the government's success.